maxiofs (0.5.0-beta) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Major feature release: Bucket Replication, Advanced Logging & Test Coverage
  * Bucket Replication System - S3-compatible cross-bucket replication
  * Support for AWS S3, MinIO, and other MaxIOFS instances as destinations
  * Three replication modes: Realtime, Scheduled (interval-based), Batch (manual)
  * Queue-based async processing with configurable worker pools
  * Automatic retry with exponential backoff for failed replications
  * Conflict resolution strategies (Last Write Wins, Version-Based, Primary Wins)
  * Selective replication with prefix filters and delete/metadata toggles
  * Priority-based rule ordering for multiple replication targets
  * SQLite persistence for rules, queue items, and replication status
  * Web Console integration with visual rule management in bucket settings tab
  * Console API endpoints for complete replication rule CRUD operations
  * Replication module with 23 automated tests (100% pass rate)
  * Advanced Logging System - HTTP and Syslog output support
  * HTTP output with batching, authentication (Bearer tokens), and flush intervals
  * Syslog integration supporting TCP and UDP protocols
  * Dynamic log configuration without server restart
  * Multiple output formats (JSON, text) with caller information
  * Prefix/suffix filters for targeted log routing to different outputs
  * Comprehensive Test Coverage Expansion (458 → 504 backend tests, ~53% coverage)
  * ACL Module Test Suite - 25 tests covering S3 ACLs and permissions (77.0% coverage)
  * Middleware Module Test Suite - 30 tests for logging, rate limiting, CORS (87.4%)
  * Lifecycle Module Test Suite - 12 tests for worker and policy processing (67.9%)
  * Storage Module Test Suite - 40 tests for filesystem operations (79.1%)
  * Metadata Module Test Suite - Expanded to 30 tests (52.4% coverage)
  * Bucket Module Test Suite - 47 tests for bucket operations (49.8% coverage)
  * Object Module Test Suite - 83 additional tests for lock and retention (48.4%)
  * Bug Fixes - Frontend session management (unexpected logout prevention)
  * Bug Fix - VEEAM SOSAPI capacity reporting now respects tenant quotas
  * Bug Fix - ListObjectVersions now works correctly for non-versioned buckets
  * Bug Fix - Console API test coverage expanded (4.4% → 12.7%, +19 tests)
  * Schema migration system for replication database (old → new S3 parameters)
  * Complete documentation updates (README, CHANGELOG, TODO, 9 docs/ files)

