maxiofs (0.4.1-beta) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Major feature release: Server-Side Encryption (SSE)
  * AES-256-CTR encryption at rest for all stored objects
  * Persistent master key storage in config.yaml (survives restarts)
  * Streaming encryption with constant memory usage (~32KB)
  * Dual-level encryption control (server + bucket settings)
  * Automatic decryption transparent to S3 clients
  * Backward compatible (mixed encrypted/unencrypted objects)
  * Industry-standard AES-256 (NIST approved, FIPS 140-2 compliant)
  * Dynamic settings system with SQLite storage
  * Metrics historical storage migrated to BadgerDB
  * Fixed critical security bugs (tenant menu, admin privileges)
  * Fixed password change detection and permission validation
  * Enhanced UI with unified card design and encryption indicators
  * Complete documentation updates (9+ docs files)

